{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17472527","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17472527"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T21:59:31+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T21:59:31+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1544"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1544","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1544"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.28,0.09,0.45,0.12,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1544"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"51685"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1544","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1544"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1544"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"36987"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"9"},{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"818"},{"type":"tags","id":"1087"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"8118"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"3290"},{"type":"contributions","id":"3333"},{"type":"contributions","id":"14868"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35525"},{"type":"contributions","id":"48783"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"51685","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/51685"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 21-month-old girl presents to the Emergency Department with a three day history of cough, runny nose and lethargy. She was previously well, has no diagnosed medical conditions and does not take any regular medications. Her birth was uncomplicated, with no abnormalities on perinatal screening. She has had two episodes of bronchiolitis in the past 12 months.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she has a pulse rate of 130/min, respiratory rate of 45/min, a SpO2 of 89% on room air and a temperature of 37.4\u00b0C. Cardiorespiratory exam reveals increased work of breathing and abnormal auscultatory findings. A chest X-ray is ordered (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is demonstrated on her chest X-ray?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Peribronchial wall thickening","Right lower lobe consolidation or collapse","Right middle lobe consolidation or collapse","Thymic shadow","Pulmonary hypertension"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe chest X-ray shows obliteration of the right heart border in keeping with \u003Cstrong\u003Eright middle lobe consolidation or collapse\u003C/strong\u003E (image). This should be assessed further with a lateral chest X-ray view. It is hard to appreciate in this image, but air bronchograms are suggestive of consolidation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPeribronchial wall thickening\u003C/strong\u003E look like opaque circles or tubular shapes in the lung parenchyma, often representing airway inflammation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ethymic shadow\u003C/strong\u003E is common for children aged less than two years of age, but is seen more superiorly and does not obliterate the heart border.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELower lobe consolidation or collapse\u003C/strong\u003E is suspected when there is loss of the diaphragm outline.\u00a0\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPulmonary hypertension\u003C/strong\u003E CXR findings include right atrial or pulmonary artery enlargement and elevated cardiac apex due to right ventricular hypertrophy.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Right middle lobe consolidation or collapse obscures the right heart border."],"references":["Ruuskanen O, Lahti E, Jennings LC, Murdoch DR. Viral pneumonia. Lancet. 2011;377(9773):1264-75. Available at: https://www.thelancet.com/article/S0140-6736(10)61459-6/fulltext"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"36987"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1544"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"1776"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"20988"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"1776","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/1776"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/ed6343ab-efd3-4590-a772-91b060f381b7.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/ed6343ab-efd3-4590-a772-91b060f381b7.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":780,"height":600}},{"type":"media","id":"20988","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/20988"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/UCbSeNhYPM2zfAidfVpUlvjvF8fSsT.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/UCbSeNhYPM2zfAidfVpUlvjvF8fSsT.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":780,"height":600}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"36987","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/36987"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-08-28T10:17:36+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-07T09:16:49+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1544"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"51685"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"9","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/9"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc76","name":"Paediatrics","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-01-16T08:39:03+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"11","links":{"se